WEBVTT

00:00:54.827 --> 00:00:57.246
EPISODE 2

00:01:15.264 --> 00:01:16.932
TRANQUILIZER

00:01:26.191 --> 00:01:27.401
DO EUN-HYUK

00:01:28.944 --> 00:01:29.820
Hello?

00:01:30.696 --> 00:01:31.572
Seol-ah.

00:01:33.574 --> 00:01:34.408
Where are you right now?

00:01:35.284 --> 00:01:36.452
Why?

00:01:38.037 --> 00:01:38.996
Seung-jae…

00:01:42.082 --> 00:01:43.250
was in an accident.

00:01:45.419 --> 00:01:47.004
Can you come to the dock right now?

00:01:58.766 --> 00:02:00.434
I think someone died.

00:02:00.517 --> 00:02:01.477
Oh, no.

00:02:38.764 --> 00:02:40.015
It's him.

00:02:45.020 --> 00:02:46.063
He was my fiancé.

00:02:47.982 --> 00:02:48.941
Did you already know?

00:02:49.441 --> 00:02:52.236
That he canceled his policy
before he died?

00:02:53.070 --> 00:02:53.904
Yes.

00:02:56.782 --> 00:02:57.700
What a shame.

00:02:57.783 --> 00:02:59.618
If he hadn't canceled it,

00:03:00.285 --> 00:03:02.538
you could've held 700 million won
in your hands.

00:03:02.621 --> 00:03:04.164
You must have a lot of time on your hands

00:03:05.332 --> 00:03:07.584
to investigate a canceled policy.

00:03:08.711 --> 00:03:10.129
You couldn't receive the death benefit,

00:03:10.713 --> 00:03:14.133
but the 200 million won premium
was returned to Mr. Yoon's account.

00:03:14.925 --> 00:03:17.636
And you're assuming
that money came my way?

00:03:19.555 --> 00:03:22.975
You think I killed my fiancé
for a measly 200 million won?

00:03:25.477 --> 00:03:26.895
Tell me.

00:03:26.979 --> 00:03:30.941
What does his accident
have to do with what happened to Ms. Kim?

00:03:39.116 --> 00:03:40.576
I can smell it.

00:03:42.786 --> 00:03:43.912
The stench of someone…

00:03:46.248 --> 00:03:47.958
trading human lives for money.

00:03:51.336 --> 00:03:52.379
Seol-ah.

00:03:56.091 --> 00:03:57.384
What are you doing?

00:03:57.468 --> 00:03:58.385
Who are you?

00:03:59.219 --> 00:04:00.721
You're the one who interrupted us.

00:04:00.804 --> 00:04:02.473
Who do you think you are
to treat Seol-ah--

00:04:02.556 --> 00:04:03.390
Don't.

00:04:08.687 --> 00:04:10.981
Do you, by any chance,
know Mr. Yoon Seung-jae as well?

00:04:11.774 --> 00:04:14.526
I'd like to talk to you.
Can I get your contact number?

00:04:20.407 --> 00:04:21.825
I'll give you my business card, then.

00:04:28.373 --> 00:04:29.333
I'll be waiting.

00:04:57.069 --> 00:04:58.237
You didn't eat again, did you?

00:04:58.987 --> 00:04:59.905
Give me a minute.

00:05:05.077 --> 00:05:06.912
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE
SIU SENIOR MANAGER CHA WOO-SEOK

00:05:09.123 --> 00:05:11.333
Why did an SIU investigator
come to see you?

00:05:12.793 --> 00:05:14.002
And what was all that about Seung-jae?

00:05:15.003 --> 00:05:18.298
It seems Kim Yun-ji and Seung-jae
had insurance with that company.

00:05:19.258 --> 00:05:20.384
Insurance?

00:05:28.142 --> 00:05:28.976
"Seiren"?

00:05:29.560 --> 00:05:32.896
You know, mermaids that lured sailors
with their singing.

00:05:34.398 --> 00:05:36.650
Oh, I think I remember that
from Greek mythology.

00:05:38.902 --> 00:05:40.362
I found that story amusing.

00:05:40.946 --> 00:05:42.406
I wonder why those men

00:05:42.489 --> 00:05:45.284
jumped into the water despite knowing
it'd lead to their deaths.

00:05:48.120 --> 00:05:49.121
Is that why

00:05:49.204 --> 00:05:50.998
you made it your restaurant logo?

00:05:52.040 --> 00:05:53.041
Yeah.

00:06:02.801 --> 00:06:05.888
Seol-ah doesn't fully open herself.

00:06:09.183 --> 00:06:13.187
There are times when she feels unfamiliar,
as if I'm seeing her for the first time,

00:06:13.937 --> 00:06:15.606
and as if she could vanish one day.

00:06:21.528 --> 00:06:22.362
Seung-jae…

00:06:24.573 --> 00:06:27.492
are you still worried
she won't accept your proposal?

00:06:30.287 --> 00:06:31.121
Actually…

00:06:32.831 --> 00:06:34.958
I took out a life insurance policy
with Seol-ah as the beneficiary.

00:06:48.513 --> 00:06:49.932
EUN-HYE

00:07:34.518 --> 00:07:36.019
KIM YUN-JI
AUCTIONEER AT ROYAL AUCTION

00:07:36.103 --> 00:07:38.438
DATE OF DEATH: AUGUST 26, 2025
POLICY ISSUE DATE: AUGUST 10, 2023

00:07:38.522 --> 00:07:40.649
PUSHED? ACCIDENT? SUICIDE?
TIP CALL BEFORE DEATH

00:07:42.192 --> 00:07:45.946
What does his accident
have to do with what happened to Yun-ji?

00:07:46.029 --> 00:07:47.739
YOON SEUNG-JAE, OWNER OF THE GALLERY
DATE OF DEATH: AUGUST 17, 2025

00:07:47.823 --> 00:07:49.533
BENEFICIARY: HAN SEOL-AH
CHEONGYANG RIVER YACHT ACCIDENT: DROWNED?

00:07:52.286 --> 00:07:54.788
And you're assuming
that money came my way?

00:07:56.915 --> 00:08:00.544
You think I killed my fiancé
for a measly 200 million won?

00:08:18.103 --> 00:08:19.938
These are the newly arrived pieces.

00:08:24.192 --> 00:08:25.861
And the condition report for these?

00:08:25.944 --> 00:08:28.322
I found the file on Ms. Kim's computer.

00:08:28.405 --> 00:08:29.531
I'll take care of it.

00:08:29.614 --> 00:08:31.867
I appreciate it, Sang-mi.

00:08:31.950 --> 00:08:32.784
Of course.

00:08:33.368 --> 00:08:34.244
Also,

00:08:34.828 --> 00:08:35.912
about that…

00:08:38.206 --> 00:08:39.207
What should we do with it?

00:08:42.127 --> 00:08:43.670
COMMUNITY CHAT SEARCH
RISK LIFE FOR MONEY

00:08:43.754 --> 00:08:45.464
Anyone willing to risk their life
for money?

00:08:46.757 --> 00:08:47.799
Must be in Cheongun.

00:08:47.883 --> 00:08:50.594
Recruiting a hitter
with a clean insurance record.

00:08:51.470 --> 00:08:52.554
What's the rate?

00:08:53.347 --> 00:08:55.140
If we go easy,
about three million won per person.

00:08:56.350 --> 00:08:57.225
I'm in.

00:08:57.976 --> 00:08:58.977
What car do you have?

00:08:59.061 --> 00:09:00.687
It's less suspicious if it's expensive.

00:09:04.232 --> 00:09:05.734
It's a foreign-made car, of course.

00:09:06.568 --> 00:09:08.987
Yes, I'll get back to you shortly.

00:09:10.655 --> 00:09:12.366
-Mr. Cha.
-Yeah?

00:09:12.449 --> 00:09:15.494
Ms. Kim Yun-ji's family
had no idea about her insurance policy.

00:09:23.585 --> 00:09:25.128
Take all the time you need.

00:09:26.630 --> 00:09:27.506
Once you get in touch,

00:09:28.173 --> 00:09:30.801
I'll make sure the insurance payout
is processed smoothly.

00:09:33.095 --> 00:09:34.262
Thank you.

00:09:35.347 --> 00:09:36.431
Thank you, but…

00:09:37.724 --> 00:09:40.102
I'd pay a hundred times that amount

00:09:41.520 --> 00:09:43.647
if it'd bring my child back.

00:09:44.523 --> 00:09:46.775
My precious daughter is gone.

00:09:47.484 --> 00:09:49.444
What's the point of any of this?

00:10:08.171 --> 00:10:09.089
I'll take that.

00:10:10.132 --> 00:10:11.591
It's heavy.

00:10:11.675 --> 00:10:12.801
I'm sorry for the trouble.

00:10:14.094 --> 00:10:15.178
Let me carry it for you.

00:10:19.141 --> 00:10:20.642
He's from the insurance company.

00:10:22.936 --> 00:10:23.812
Where should I put it?

00:10:24.396 --> 00:10:25.313
This way, please.

00:10:40.996 --> 00:10:42.914
It feels like she'll be back any moment,

00:10:43.748 --> 00:10:45.250
so I left everything just as it is.

00:10:46.543 --> 00:10:47.502
Over here, please.

00:10:56.219 --> 00:10:58.430
There are a lot of company documents.

00:10:58.513 --> 00:11:01.016
You can take them with you
if you need them.

00:11:01.933 --> 00:11:03.435
Okay, I will.

00:11:04.394 --> 00:11:05.395
All right, then.

00:11:06.062 --> 00:11:07.189
Take a look around.

00:11:08.899 --> 00:11:11.067
I'll prepare some tea for you
in the living room.

00:11:54.236 --> 00:11:55.820
H2 2025 GLOBAL ART TRENDS REPORT

00:12:29.187 --> 00:12:30.897
Can you step out for a bit?

00:12:32.023 --> 00:12:32.857
Why?

00:12:32.941 --> 00:12:34.985
Do you want to rummage on your own?

00:12:35.068 --> 00:12:36.695
Didn't you hear what her mother said?

00:12:37.404 --> 00:12:39.239
She told me to take the company documents.

00:12:59.801 --> 00:13:02.679
HAN SEOL-AH BUSINESS TRIP

00:13:02.762 --> 00:13:04.681
HAN SEOL-AH MEETING
WITH SU GALLERY MANAGER

00:13:06.391 --> 00:13:08.768
HAN SEOL-AH ON LEAVE

00:13:11.438 --> 00:13:13.481
OUT OF THE OFFICE ALL DAY
MAYBE A VIP CLIENT MEETING?

00:13:21.656 --> 00:13:24.826
She didn't smile once
after joining Royal Auction.

00:13:25.660 --> 00:13:27.120
I thought it was rather strange

00:13:27.203 --> 00:13:29.831
when she left the TV station

00:13:29.914 --> 00:13:32.125
and suddenly decided to work
at an auction house.

00:13:35.545 --> 00:13:36.755
What kind of person

00:13:37.922 --> 00:13:39.591
was Ms. Kim at work?

00:13:45.597 --> 00:13:47.265
She was hard-working.

00:13:48.975 --> 00:13:50.727
I heard she was about to get promoted.

00:13:52.270 --> 00:13:53.563
I just don't understand.

00:13:54.105 --> 00:13:56.232
When a suicide takes place at a company,

00:13:57.400 --> 00:13:58.652
there's usually a message behind it.

00:13:59.527 --> 00:14:02.781
For example, workplace bullying,
conflict between colleagues,

00:14:02.864 --> 00:14:03.698
or being wronged.

00:14:03.782 --> 00:14:05.825
But you're saying
it was none of these things.

00:14:06.409 --> 00:14:07.786
Then I wonder what it was.

00:14:08.912 --> 00:14:10.997
I don't know
everyone's personal matters at work.

00:14:15.043 --> 00:14:18.213
Do you have any idea
what it could've been?

00:14:19.923 --> 00:14:20.757
There's one thing…

00:14:22.884 --> 00:14:24.427
that comes to mind.

00:14:37.399 --> 00:14:39.901
Why are you out all night these days?

00:14:40.944 --> 00:14:43.405
Get up and have a bite to eat
before you sleep.

00:14:55.959 --> 00:14:56.835
Are you…

00:14:58.086 --> 00:14:59.713
seeing that man again?

00:15:01.589 --> 00:15:02.924
Were you with him?

00:15:05.009 --> 00:15:07.220
What's wrong, Yun-ji?

00:15:11.850 --> 00:15:14.686
Do you know the man Yun-ji was seeing?

00:15:19.691 --> 00:15:20.984
A man?

00:15:21.693 --> 00:15:23.737
I'm her mother, but I don't know anything.

00:15:26.489 --> 00:15:28.491
I don't know why
she was suffering so much,

00:15:29.242 --> 00:15:31.786
or why she chose to end things.

00:15:31.870 --> 00:15:33.079
ASSOCIATE AUCTIONEER KIM YUN-JI

00:15:33.163 --> 00:15:36.916
I'm her mother, but I don't know anything.

00:15:43.006 --> 00:15:44.924
I'm sure you went through
everything at work.

00:15:47.010 --> 00:15:49.304
Did you come to check
if she left something at home?

00:15:49.888 --> 00:15:51.473
You came to check first,

00:15:51.556 --> 00:15:52.807
but I guess you didn't find anything.

00:15:53.391 --> 00:15:54.851
You want to know what I found?

00:15:55.769 --> 00:15:56.770
I could tell you.

00:15:57.395 --> 00:15:58.730
Keep it to yourself.

00:15:58.813 --> 00:16:01.065
I don't care what you came here to do,

00:16:01.149 --> 00:16:04.486
but I find it offensive to be questioned
before a mother who lost her daughter.

00:16:04.569 --> 00:16:06.988
Shouldn't you be more cooperative
as her immediate supervisor?

00:16:07.071 --> 00:16:09.574
I've already cooperated with the police.

00:16:09.657 --> 00:16:11.743
And I have no interest
in prying into the private life

00:16:12.285 --> 00:16:13.244
of the deceased.

00:16:14.037 --> 00:16:15.789
I'm trying to find out

00:16:17.248 --> 00:16:18.833
whether or not it was a wrongful death.

00:16:20.710 --> 00:16:21.795
Wrongful death?

00:16:25.924 --> 00:16:27.091
What about wrongful suspicion?

00:16:28.843 --> 00:16:31.679
You never know
who the real victim might be.

00:17:10.134 --> 00:17:12.470
VIOLENT CRIMES UNIT 1

00:17:13.930 --> 00:17:14.973
CALL LOG
NAME: KIM YUN-JI

00:17:16.683 --> 00:17:18.434
YOON SEUNG-JAE

00:17:19.018 --> 00:17:20.395
YOON SEUNG-JAE

00:17:25.024 --> 00:17:26.150
Yoon Seung-jae.

00:17:26.776 --> 00:17:27.902
Yoon Seung-jae.

00:17:28.611 --> 00:17:29.821
Yoon Seung-jae again.

00:17:31.823 --> 00:17:34.033
Hey, Ggong.
You've heard of Yoon Seung-jae, right?

00:17:34.117 --> 00:17:37.120
Yes, I left the Cheongun Police Station
investigation report on your desk.

00:17:37.662 --> 00:17:38.663
Investigation report?

00:17:40.915 --> 00:17:42.917
GANGNAM "A CLUB" VIP NARCOTICS CASE
GANGHA POLICE STATION

00:17:45.753 --> 00:17:49.173
YOON SEUNG-JAE DEATH CASE

00:17:52.594 --> 00:17:56.389
BODY FOUND FLOATING IN WATER
BODY IDENTIFIED BY FIANCÉE (HAN SEOL-AH)

00:18:09.319 --> 00:18:11.529
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

00:18:11.613 --> 00:18:13.948
2025 CERTIFIED
INSURANCE FRAUD INVESTIGATOR

00:18:19.579 --> 00:18:21.831
Don't tell me he hasn't come to work yet.

00:18:22.373 --> 00:18:24.626
Does he not know the quarter-end
is right around the corner?

00:18:25.209 --> 00:18:26.586
That little punk.

00:18:27.170 --> 00:18:28.171
Hey, Cha.

00:18:29.047 --> 00:18:30.214
Where the hell are you?!

00:18:32.800 --> 00:18:34.052
Oh, I see.

00:18:34.135 --> 00:18:36.512
Of course, you have to spend money.

00:18:37.764 --> 00:18:39.474
Right, right. Be careful, okay?

00:18:40.850 --> 00:18:41.684
What did he say?

00:18:41.768 --> 00:18:43.227
He's bringing in a big one.

00:18:46.439 --> 00:18:49.233
I'm so done being stuck in this office.

00:18:49.317 --> 00:18:50.735
I'm getting out of here!

00:18:50.818 --> 00:18:51.653
I can do this!

00:18:53.154 --> 00:18:54.238
"The Purpose of Insurance."

00:19:04.832 --> 00:19:09.754
CHEONGUN, WHERE LIFE IS GOOD

00:19:09.837 --> 00:19:11.714
All right, the backers are here and ready.

00:19:11.798 --> 00:19:12.632
Where are you, Mr. Hitter?

00:19:13.341 --> 00:19:15.009
I'm 500 meters behind.

00:19:15.551 --> 00:19:16.719
This is your first time, right?

00:19:16.803 --> 00:19:19.347
I'll go straight,
then turn right, and brake hard,

00:19:19.430 --> 00:19:21.140
so be bold and don't hold back.

00:19:21.224 --> 00:19:22.517
Just ram into us, okay?

00:19:23.977 --> 00:19:25.603
But you're in a compact car.

00:19:25.687 --> 00:19:28.564
Just go for it. We won't die.

00:19:29.816 --> 00:19:31.985
I'll hit you full force, then.

00:19:32.068 --> 00:19:32.944
Okay.

00:19:33.569 --> 00:19:34.696
What's your plate number again?

00:19:35.279 --> 00:19:36.364
It's 7622.

00:19:36.447 --> 00:19:38.199
Got it.

00:19:38.282 --> 00:19:39.450
Follow us, but don't make it obvious.

00:19:39.993 --> 00:19:41.077
Hey, let's go.

00:19:54.340 --> 00:19:55.883
What's taking him so long?

00:19:57.552 --> 00:19:59.929
Damn it, why isn't Cha Woo-seok here yet?

00:20:01.014 --> 00:20:04.600
-Hey, move over, will you?
-Sit still, for crying out loud.

00:20:04.684 --> 00:20:06.144
-Why isn't he coming?
-Why is it so tight in here?

00:20:06.227 --> 00:20:07.603
Where is he?

00:20:08.187 --> 00:20:10.314
Hey, where are you?
You said you had a foreign-made car.

00:20:10.898 --> 00:20:12.233
I do.

00:20:12.316 --> 00:20:13.985
It's just a bit big.

00:20:14.068 --> 00:20:15.403
What the hell are you saying?

00:20:29.000 --> 00:20:30.460
What the hell? It's 7622!

00:20:32.211 --> 00:20:33.129
That's him!

00:20:33.212 --> 00:20:35.339
-Hey, step on it!
-What the hell?

00:20:35.923 --> 00:20:37.467
What the hell is with him?

00:20:37.550 --> 00:20:39.177
-Just go!
-Go!

00:20:39.260 --> 00:20:40.595
-Speed it up!
-Step on it!

00:20:42.096 --> 00:20:43.639
Go faster!

00:20:44.182 --> 00:20:45.767
Step on it already!

00:20:45.850 --> 00:20:47.643
I told you to lose some weight!

00:20:47.727 --> 00:20:49.687
-He's going to hit us!
-Go, go, go!

00:20:52.273 --> 00:20:53.983
Hey, move to the side!

00:20:55.026 --> 00:20:56.444
I told you to lose some weight, idiot!

00:20:56.527 --> 00:20:57.403
Hey!

00:20:57.487 --> 00:20:59.614
You crazy bastard! Stop right now!

00:21:00.114 --> 00:21:01.949
-Hey!
-Step on it!

00:21:02.033 --> 00:21:03.326
He's closing in!

00:21:03.409 --> 00:21:05.495
-Go faster!
-He's going to hit us!

00:21:07.622 --> 00:21:09.624
Go faster, come on!

00:21:09.707 --> 00:21:11.334
Speed up!

00:21:11.417 --> 00:21:12.627
Step on it!

00:21:14.670 --> 00:21:16.422
-Go faster!
-He's coming!

00:21:17.715 --> 00:21:18.549
Step on it!

00:21:20.927 --> 00:21:23.137
This is my goddamn car!

00:21:25.014 --> 00:21:26.641
-Watch it!
-Holy crap!

00:21:32.146 --> 00:21:33.231
Oh, jeez.

00:21:39.821 --> 00:21:40.905
Damn it.

00:21:42.990 --> 00:21:44.575
Man, I feel like I'm going to die.

00:21:44.659 --> 00:21:46.327
Oh, man.

00:21:46.410 --> 00:21:47.662
What are you all looking at?

00:21:51.499 --> 00:21:53.084
It's nothing. Go back inside.

00:21:54.460 --> 00:21:55.586
Oh, dear.

00:21:55.670 --> 00:21:57.171
I was going to hit you from behind,

00:21:57.255 --> 00:21:59.132
but you crashed into the truck
in front of you.

00:21:59.215 --> 00:22:00.299
Hey.

00:22:00.383 --> 00:22:02.093
Were you trying to kill or something?

00:22:02.176 --> 00:22:03.136
Yeah.

00:22:03.219 --> 00:22:05.304
-How'd you know?
-Hey.

00:22:05.888 --> 00:22:06.764
Hey.

00:22:06.848 --> 00:22:08.808
Oh, let me introduce you to each other.

00:22:09.475 --> 00:22:12.311
This is Detective Kim
from Cheongun Police Station.

00:22:12.395 --> 00:22:14.939
And this is the Cheongun Family Gang,

00:22:15.022 --> 00:22:16.315
an insurance fraud ring.

00:22:16.899 --> 00:22:18.192
Oh, I see.

00:22:20.194 --> 00:22:21.320
An insurance fraud ring, huh?

00:22:21.404 --> 00:22:23.614
-Cops?
-Nice to meet you.

00:22:23.698 --> 00:22:26.534
-All right, let's go.
-That hurts!

00:22:28.494 --> 00:22:30.955
-Come on.
-That hurts!

00:22:31.038 --> 00:22:33.082
-See you.
-Go already.

00:22:34.292 --> 00:22:35.877
No wonder you wanted to meet

00:22:35.960 --> 00:22:37.962
at such a random place
instead of the station.

00:22:41.215 --> 00:22:42.049
Here.

00:22:44.177 --> 00:22:45.720
Files on all the scams
they've pulled off so far

00:22:45.803 --> 00:22:47.263
and CCTV footage.

00:22:47.346 --> 00:22:48.514
Man.

00:22:48.598 --> 00:22:49.640
This is just what I needed.

00:22:49.724 --> 00:22:51.601
A guy like you
should've stayed on as a detective.

00:22:53.352 --> 00:22:55.062
Let me show you
what you asked me to look into.

00:22:56.522 --> 00:22:59.108
When I got there, he was already dead.

00:22:59.817 --> 00:23:00.818
It was an accidental death.

00:23:01.861 --> 00:23:04.030
Are you sure Yoon Seung-jae
was alone on the yacht?

00:23:04.113 --> 00:23:04.947
Yeah.

00:23:05.031 --> 00:23:08.784
There were a lot of witnesses,
including the dock manager and fishermen.

00:23:09.994 --> 00:23:11.996
-Then the autopsy results must also--
-Death by drowning.

00:23:12.622 --> 00:23:15.583
I think he accidentally fell overboard
and struck the propellers.

00:23:16.959 --> 00:23:18.836
The case itself isn't strange,

00:23:18.920 --> 00:23:20.296
but that woman was a bit…

00:23:22.256 --> 00:23:23.299
Here it is.

00:23:25.801 --> 00:23:28.763
His family was overseas at the time,

00:23:28.846 --> 00:23:31.015
so his fiancée came to identify the body.

00:23:32.683 --> 00:23:35.228
I worried she might pass out
because the body was severely damaged,

00:23:35.311 --> 00:23:36.896
but she didn't even bat an eye.

00:24:33.536 --> 00:24:34.370
Here.

00:24:35.579 --> 00:24:37.290
I canceled the insurance policy,

00:24:37.873 --> 00:24:38.874
so don't worry.

00:25:03.274 --> 00:25:05.901
CHAIR KIM

00:25:07.486 --> 00:25:08.321
I always make sure

00:25:09.322 --> 00:25:13.159
to include steamed sea bream
on my father's ancestral table.

00:25:13.909 --> 00:25:15.244
He must've liked it.

00:25:16.162 --> 00:25:17.621
He didn't because it was too fishy.

00:25:17.705 --> 00:25:19.332
I only make it because I want to eat it.

00:25:22.209 --> 00:25:23.044
Try some.

00:25:24.462 --> 00:25:26.547
Are you sure you didn't make it for me?

00:25:27.757 --> 00:25:29.175
Sharp as ever.

00:25:30.051 --> 00:25:33.679
Back when I used to bring raw fish
to Artist Han's studio,

00:25:33.763 --> 00:25:35.681
you were always the most excited.

00:25:35.765 --> 00:25:39.435
Even at a young age, you ate everything,
including sea squirt and sea cucumber.

00:25:41.187 --> 00:25:42.646
You seem to remember everything.

00:25:43.898 --> 00:25:46.108
You made the right call
visiting Ms. Kim's family.

00:25:47.443 --> 00:25:50.321
It takes that kind of thinking
to protect a company.

00:25:50.988 --> 00:25:54.909
Workplace bullying
is such a big topic these days.

00:25:56.285 --> 00:25:58.454
-How did you--
-They called to say thank you.

00:25:59.038 --> 00:26:01.582
Did you know her father
works at the National Tax Service?

00:26:01.665 --> 00:26:05.169
If he set his mind to it,
he could easily take down our company.

00:26:07.797 --> 00:26:10.716
From what I've heard, her death seems to
have been caused by personal matters.

00:26:10.800 --> 00:26:13.719
Her mother didn't harbor
any resentment toward us.

00:26:13.803 --> 00:26:16.347
She appeared to be having
a hard time though.

00:26:17.139 --> 00:26:18.641
You're having a hard time too.

00:26:19.642 --> 00:26:21.268
I heard you lost your fiancé
in an accident.

00:26:21.852 --> 00:26:23.187
If something like that happened,

00:26:23.854 --> 00:26:26.399
you should've told me
and taken some time off.

00:26:28.818 --> 00:26:31.904
It was better for me to focus on work.

00:26:35.241 --> 00:26:36.450
You poor thing.

00:26:41.205 --> 00:26:43.624
Here, eat up while it's still warm.

00:27:47.480 --> 00:27:50.274
I called you earlier.
I'm Cha Woo-seok, an SIU investigator.

00:27:51.525 --> 00:27:52.776
What is this about?

00:27:52.860 --> 00:27:55.488
I'm investigating matters
involving Mr. Yoon Seung-jae's insurance.

00:27:56.906 --> 00:27:58.449
I believe he had a fiancée?

00:27:59.825 --> 00:28:00.701
Yes, I know her.

00:28:01.410 --> 00:28:02.453
Seol-ah.

00:28:03.621 --> 00:28:04.622
Do you happen to know

00:28:05.456 --> 00:28:06.916
Ms. Kim Yun-ji as well?

00:28:08.000 --> 00:28:08.876
Who?

00:28:12.796 --> 00:28:13.631
This person.

00:28:15.007 --> 00:28:16.133
Oh, I've seen her before.

00:28:16.217 --> 00:28:18.177
I remember her
because she's been coming by often.

00:28:19.011 --> 00:28:20.888
Ms. Kim Yun-ji has been here?

00:28:20.971 --> 00:28:22.014
What for?

00:28:22.097 --> 00:28:23.849
I wouldn't know.

00:28:28.812 --> 00:28:30.940
What was her relationship with Mr. Yoon?

00:28:31.023 --> 00:28:32.816
Did it look like
they'd known each other long?

00:28:32.900 --> 00:28:34.818
They didn't seem close.

00:28:34.902 --> 00:28:37.446
Mr. Yoon didn't seem that fond of her.

00:28:39.365 --> 00:28:40.533
When was her last visit?

00:28:42.368 --> 00:28:44.495
The day before Mr. Yoon's accident.

00:28:44.578 --> 00:28:46.539
She came by again

00:28:46.622 --> 00:28:49.833
and waited until we closed,
saying she had something to tell him.

00:28:53.212 --> 00:28:54.213
She sat over there.

00:30:12.916 --> 00:30:15.961
When I got there, he was already dead.

00:30:16.045 --> 00:30:17.338
It was an accidental death.

00:30:38.692 --> 00:30:41.320
Kim Yun-ji and Yoon Seung-jae met,

00:30:42.488 --> 00:30:44.156
and they both died

00:30:45.658 --> 00:30:46.825
in just ten days.

00:30:49.745 --> 00:30:51.455
I didn't know you were so competent.

00:30:54.333 --> 00:30:56.377
It's normal for the police
to have reasonable suspicions.

00:30:56.877 --> 00:30:58.212
But why would an SIU investigator

00:30:58.754 --> 00:31:01.256
chase after a case
where a payout was never made?

00:31:03.258 --> 00:31:04.635
That's the problem with you, Seong-il.

00:31:05.511 --> 00:31:07.012
You lack imagination.

00:31:08.138 --> 00:31:09.264
You think this was the first time?

00:31:10.307 --> 00:31:11.850
This is why you're always one step behind.

00:31:14.228 --> 00:31:16.563
Ever thought that your imagination
might be the problem?

00:31:17.147 --> 00:31:18.899
Like the delusion
about your sister's death

00:31:19.733 --> 00:31:20.567
being a murder.

00:31:23.821 --> 00:31:26.281
As the detective in charge,
you don't want to admit incompetence,

00:31:26.365 --> 00:31:27.616
yet you want peace of mind.

00:31:28.909 --> 00:31:29.743
Yeah.

00:31:30.577 --> 00:31:31.704
I get it.

00:31:33.038 --> 00:31:34.206
But are you really at peace?

00:32:05.821 --> 00:32:07.114
What are you thinking about?

00:32:08.407 --> 00:32:10.284
Stop worrying about me.

00:32:10.367 --> 00:32:11.493
I'm not.

00:32:11.577 --> 00:32:13.787
You are. It's written all over your face.

00:32:13.871 --> 00:32:16.039
I didn't lie like my friends did

00:32:16.123 --> 00:32:17.875
and was honest about
taking a trip with my boyfriend.

00:32:19.668 --> 00:32:21.712
Jeez, when did you grow up?

00:32:21.795 --> 00:32:23.213
I think I'll get married before you.

00:32:26.008 --> 00:32:27.050
Ms. Cha Woo-hee.

00:32:27.718 --> 00:32:29.595
Marriage already? Control yourself.

00:33:16.600 --> 00:33:17.768
I'll have what she's having.

00:33:43.001 --> 00:33:45.712
Did you know Kim Yun-ji went to see
Yoon Seung-jae at his restaurant?

00:33:48.382 --> 00:33:49.633
On the day before the accident, at that.

00:33:53.804 --> 00:33:54.930
So?

00:33:56.890 --> 00:33:58.225
Why did those two meet?

00:34:00.936 --> 00:34:03.480
You can't know everything about someone,
no matter how close you are to them.

00:34:06.233 --> 00:34:07.568
So you have no idea?

00:34:09.653 --> 00:34:11.154
Then what could it be?

00:34:12.239 --> 00:34:15.993
What reason was there for your fiancé
and colleague to meet secretly?

00:34:17.828 --> 00:34:19.913
It didn't seem like
they were just acquaintances.

00:34:21.582 --> 00:34:22.583
Were they

00:34:23.709 --> 00:34:25.586
involved or something?

00:34:35.637 --> 00:34:37.055
You kill out of love,

00:34:37.764 --> 00:34:40.767
you kill out of hate, and you want to kill
as much as you love.

00:34:42.978 --> 00:34:45.063
The most common motive for murder
is love affairs.

00:34:47.900 --> 00:34:48.734
Love affairs?

00:34:50.027 --> 00:34:51.153
Not a fan of that theory?

00:34:51.737 --> 00:34:53.697
Then what about
premeditated murder for money?

00:34:58.660 --> 00:35:00.996
Do you know what insurance scammers
have in common?

00:35:02.706 --> 00:35:04.875
Once they've had a taste of money,
they want more.

00:35:04.958 --> 00:35:07.044
They want bigger money
through easier means.

00:35:07.127 --> 00:35:10.714
Then things escalate, and they get bolder,
so bold that people start to notice.

00:35:13.008 --> 00:35:14.968
-What does that have to do with--
-Ms. Han Seol-ah.

00:35:16.720 --> 00:35:18.096
I'm investigating a tip I received.

00:35:19.348 --> 00:35:22.476
A tip claiming that Yoon Seung-jae's death
was a case of murder-for-insurance.

00:35:28.857 --> 00:35:30.400
I see Ms. Kim Yun-ji gave you the tip.

00:35:31.693 --> 00:35:33.278
I was supposed to meet her that night.

00:35:34.571 --> 00:35:35.530
But she goes and commits suicide?

00:35:38.075 --> 00:35:39.326
That makes no sense at all.

00:35:43.246 --> 00:35:44.790
Stop playing detective.

00:35:46.041 --> 00:35:48.377
I never received any insurance payout,

00:35:48.460 --> 00:35:49.294
which means

00:35:50.504 --> 00:35:52.422
I'm not the subject of your investigation.

00:35:54.967 --> 00:35:56.301
I guess I'll find the answer
if I dig deeper.

00:35:59.972 --> 00:36:01.556
What is it that you really want to know?

00:36:05.894 --> 00:36:07.938
Your fiancé and Kim Yun-ji.

00:36:12.818 --> 00:36:13.819
Did you kill them?

00:37:16.339 --> 00:37:20.135
HAN SEOL-AH IN CHEONGUN CITY

00:37:24.931 --> 00:37:27.851
HAN SEOL-AH, KIM YUN-JI, YOON SEUNG-JAE

00:37:28.435 --> 00:37:29.478
A love triangle?

00:37:29.561 --> 00:37:30.812
I don't think Han Seol-ah knew.

00:37:32.856 --> 00:37:33.732
Really?

00:37:34.524 --> 00:37:35.734
Micro expressions.

00:37:37.694 --> 00:37:39.279
No matter how good your poker face is,

00:37:39.905 --> 00:37:42.157
you can't hide fleeting expressions.

00:37:43.825 --> 00:37:44.785
She didn't know.

00:37:46.995 --> 00:37:49.414
And there's no way to find out
since they're both dead.

00:37:50.332 --> 00:37:51.458
What really happened?

00:37:52.876 --> 00:37:53.919
But you know,

00:37:55.003 --> 00:37:57.756
when I asked if she killed them,
she was surprisingly unshaken.

00:37:58.340 --> 00:37:59.257
It's one or the other.

00:38:00.383 --> 00:38:01.426
Either she's innocent,

00:38:02.010 --> 00:38:03.970
or she's completely deceiving
even herself.

00:38:05.222 --> 00:38:07.808
Either way, it was just
attempted insurance fraud, right?

00:38:09.101 --> 00:38:11.311
Ju Hyun-su didn't start out
intending to commit murder either.

00:38:13.480 --> 00:38:15.816
It started with the insurance payout
from the car accident.

00:38:17.150 --> 00:38:19.861
His accident insurance got denied,
so he needed a scapegoat.

00:38:22.239 --> 00:38:23.532
And that was my sister.

00:38:25.700 --> 00:38:28.912
So you think Han Seol-ah likely received
a payout in the past as well?

00:38:30.539 --> 00:38:31.456
Probably.

00:38:56.481 --> 00:38:59.317
I heard Ms. Kim died
after an argument with Ms. Han.

00:38:59.901 --> 00:39:00.735
Really?

00:39:01.695 --> 00:39:04.364
I heard Ms. Han gave Ms. Kim
a really tough time.

00:39:28.346 --> 00:39:31.141
I sensed something might happen
from the moment you tore that painting.

00:39:32.350 --> 00:39:33.977
I can't blame her for wanting to die.

00:39:35.937 --> 00:39:37.314
I've kept quiet about this,

00:39:37.397 --> 00:39:40.859
but Ms. Kim often came to me in tears.

00:39:40.942 --> 00:39:42.068
Because of you.

00:39:43.570 --> 00:39:44.654
I see.

00:39:44.738 --> 00:39:47.240
Then why didn't you do a better job
comforting her?

00:39:47.324 --> 00:39:49.701
I guess she couldn't rely on you either.

00:39:51.995 --> 00:39:52.913
Whatever.

00:39:52.996 --> 00:39:54.831
What's important is public opinion.

00:39:56.124 --> 00:39:57.542
The real reason Kim Yun-ji died…

00:39:57.626 --> 00:39:59.502
Han Seol-ah constantly bullied Kim Yun-ji…

00:39:59.586 --> 00:40:02.005
Rumors about the chief auctioneer
replacement have been floating around…

00:40:02.088 --> 00:40:04.257
Ms. Han is Chair Kim's secret daughter?

00:40:04.341 --> 00:40:05.550
There's no way.

00:40:06.676 --> 00:40:08.094
If you want to sway public opinion,

00:40:08.178 --> 00:40:10.180
you should at least use multiple accounts.

00:40:11.431 --> 00:40:12.265
What?

00:40:13.099 --> 00:40:13.975
What did you say?

00:40:18.438 --> 00:40:19.481
Damn it.

00:40:19.981 --> 00:40:22.567
She's too damn observant.

00:40:23.818 --> 00:40:24.778
For goodness' sake.

00:40:36.039 --> 00:40:37.457
A bit higher, please.

00:40:42.629 --> 00:40:43.463
Okay.

00:40:44.047 --> 00:40:45.048
Next piece.

00:40:46.967 --> 00:40:47.842
That's good.

00:40:53.306 --> 00:40:54.140
Set the lighting to 20.

00:40:56.768 --> 00:40:57.602
Okay, next piece.

00:41:07.612 --> 00:41:10.448
-Let's take a ten-minute break.
-Okay.

00:41:17.664 --> 00:41:20.333
THE REAL REASON KIM YUN-JI DIED
RUMORS ABOUT CHIEF AUCTIONEER REPLACEMENT

00:41:22.252 --> 00:41:24.170
IS IT TRUE THAT MS. HAN IS QUITTING?

00:41:25.255 --> 00:41:26.339
What do you think?

00:41:28.508 --> 00:41:29.342
About what?

00:41:30.343 --> 00:41:33.263
I'm asking how much you can trust
your best friend, Han Seol-ah.

00:41:34.889 --> 00:41:36.308
Go back to work.

00:41:36.391 --> 00:41:38.018
She scares me now.

00:41:38.101 --> 00:41:39.936
I'm worried about you.

00:41:41.938 --> 00:41:45.025
Be honest.
You're suspecting her too, aren't you?

00:41:48.653 --> 00:41:49.487
Eun-hye.

00:41:50.780 --> 00:41:52.198
Seol-ah's the one

00:41:52.949 --> 00:41:54.367
who got you this internship.

00:41:56.036 --> 00:41:58.288
The scholarships
and training opportunities you got

00:41:58.371 --> 00:41:59.622
didn't just happen on their own.

00:42:03.043 --> 00:42:04.169
I never asked her for any of that.

00:42:04.252 --> 00:42:05.628
Who does she think she is?

00:42:06.212 --> 00:42:07.714
She considers us family.

00:42:07.797 --> 00:42:08.631
Family?

00:42:08.715 --> 00:42:11.634
She's just pretending to care about me
so she can use you.

00:42:11.718 --> 00:42:13.428
She's just keeping you around
to make you take photos.

00:42:13.511 --> 00:42:15.305
Watch what you say.

00:42:25.231 --> 00:42:26.441
This tastes good.

00:42:28.902 --> 00:42:32.072
You told me before

00:42:32.864 --> 00:42:34.491
that my mom getting money

00:42:35.158 --> 00:42:36.951
from me falling ill

00:42:37.619 --> 00:42:39.662
wouldn't make her happy,

00:42:41.247 --> 00:42:44.959
and that it'd just lead her
further down a bad path.

00:42:45.752 --> 00:42:47.712
If I tell the truth,

00:42:49.214 --> 00:42:51.174
what will happen to her?

00:42:52.550 --> 00:42:53.885
Will she get taken away?

00:42:59.849 --> 00:43:00.850
Chae-rin.

00:43:02.727 --> 00:43:04.604
The only person who can stop your mom

00:43:05.480 --> 00:43:06.356
is you.

00:43:07.941 --> 00:43:10.443
And I want to protect you

00:43:11.861 --> 00:43:13.154
so you won't hurt anymore.

00:43:17.283 --> 00:43:18.952
I'm sorry I couldn't protect you sooner.

00:43:26.084 --> 00:43:27.293
I'm fuming.

00:43:27.377 --> 00:43:29.587
How much time do you think
Chae-rin's mom will serve?

00:43:29.671 --> 00:43:32.590
Can't people like her
just be locked up for good?

00:43:32.674 --> 00:43:33.925
What kind of mother is she?

00:43:35.135 --> 00:43:37.262
I'm glad Chae-rin finally spoke up,

00:43:38.513 --> 00:43:39.848
but I'm not sure about this.

00:43:41.433 --> 00:43:42.767
No matter how terrible a mom is,

00:43:43.643 --> 00:43:45.061
a child would still miss her.

00:43:46.271 --> 00:43:48.523
But still,
we couldn't just leave her like that.

00:43:48.606 --> 00:43:49.607
We had to save her.

00:43:49.691 --> 00:43:51.860
Did we really save her though?

00:43:51.943 --> 00:43:53.862
At least we saved her from the worst.

00:43:54.863 --> 00:43:57.574
The world's a crazy place.
All this over money.

00:43:58.783 --> 00:44:00.994
I've requested her foster care
and medical support,

00:44:01.077 --> 00:44:02.245
so make sure to follow up on it.

00:44:02.328 --> 00:44:04.038
I've already prepared
the necessary documents.

00:44:10.003 --> 00:44:11.045
Hello, this is Cha Woo-seok.

00:44:11.754 --> 00:44:14.966
Mr. Cha, this is the Insurance Fraud
Prevention Team at the KLIA.

00:44:15.049 --> 00:44:16.468
It's about your inquiry on Han Seol-ah.

00:44:16.551 --> 00:44:18.470
We found a policy
taken out with HA Life Insurance.

00:44:34.694 --> 00:44:36.529
SHOCK AS DOCTOR IN 30S DIES
IN SUSPECTED PROPOFOL SELF-INJECTION

00:44:37.363 --> 00:44:40.241
NFS REVEALS, "CAUSE OF DEATH WAS
PROPOFOL OVERDOSE, NO SIGNS OF FOUL PLAY"

00:44:42.494 --> 00:44:44.037
The doctor's name was Choi Young-ho.

00:44:44.120 --> 00:44:46.289
He had a whole life insurance policy
with HA Life Insurance,

00:44:46.372 --> 00:44:48.041
and the policy was set to pay out
500 million won

00:44:48.124 --> 00:44:50.627
to his then-partner, Han Seol-ah,
upon his death.

00:44:50.710 --> 00:44:52.545
His policy was canceled
before he died too.

00:44:53.129 --> 00:44:55.548
So she didn't
get this 500 million payout either?

00:44:57.383 --> 00:44:59.677
What's up with this woman?

00:45:00.345 --> 00:45:02.180
In any case, she didn't get the payout.

00:45:02.764 --> 00:45:05.808
Two people died after taking out
huge life insurance policies,

00:45:05.892 --> 00:45:07.310
and the beneficiary is the same person.

00:45:08.019 --> 00:45:09.812
As a former police captain,
do you not find it suspicious?

00:45:09.896 --> 00:45:12.565
That's why it's even less of our concern,

00:45:12.649 --> 00:45:15.109
unless the police take an interest in it.

00:45:15.193 --> 00:45:18.112
Jeez, you've become a corporate man
through and through.

00:45:19.364 --> 00:45:20.949
Hand this over to Detective Gong.

00:45:21.032 --> 00:45:23.451
Don't bother with things
that don't count for your performance.

00:45:24.994 --> 00:45:25.828
Hey, Cha-cha.

00:45:27.205 --> 00:45:28.498
Cha-cha!

00:45:30.208 --> 00:45:33.336
I don't know why
this reminds me of that movie.

00:45:38.925 --> 00:45:39.884
What are you doing?

00:45:47.433 --> 00:45:49.060
Don't you know Basic Instinct, Mr. Koo?

00:45:49.143 --> 00:45:52.605
Maybe Han Seol-ah is like Sharon Stone
in Basic Instinct.

00:45:52.689 --> 00:45:53.898
She uses her incredible beauty

00:45:53.982 --> 00:45:55.942
to seduce men
into taking out insurance policies

00:45:56.025 --> 00:45:57.860
before killing them without mercy!

00:46:04.409 --> 00:46:05.702
Should I just kill him?

00:46:08.079 --> 00:46:09.455
An SIU investigator?

00:46:09.539 --> 00:46:10.915
ION MENTAL CLINIC

00:46:10.999 --> 00:46:14.335
I'm not sure why I need to disclose
a deceased person's personal life.

00:46:15.837 --> 00:46:16.671
You're not even with the police.

00:46:18.214 --> 00:46:20.258
Then do you know who Han Seol-ah is?

00:46:22.760 --> 00:46:24.596
We have to maintain
doctor-patient confidentiality--

00:46:24.679 --> 00:46:26.472
So she was a patient here.

00:46:28.516 --> 00:46:30.685
In any case, I have nothing to tell you.

00:46:50.079 --> 00:46:50.913
Hello.

00:46:55.835 --> 00:46:58.379
Man, I'm hungry.

00:47:07.847 --> 00:47:08.890
Ms. Kim Mi-yeon?

00:47:10.767 --> 00:47:13.394
You know something about Ms. Han Seol-ah
and Dr. Choi Young-ho, don't you?

00:47:17.065 --> 00:47:18.232
I need a few minutes of your time.

00:47:22.528 --> 00:47:23.446
It'll cost you.

00:47:33.706 --> 00:47:34.874
Depression?

00:47:37.627 --> 00:47:39.253
I guess she was hurting badly

00:47:39.837 --> 00:47:41.214
after breaking up with her boyfriend.

00:47:45.593 --> 00:47:48.805
Are you saying
she dated someone before Mr. Choi?

00:47:49.389 --> 00:47:50.223
Are you kidding me?

00:47:50.807 --> 00:47:53.601
Of course, she dated someone before him.
She's gorgeous.

00:47:54.227 --> 00:47:57.605
Dr. Choi was so head over heels for her
that he even dumped his girlfriend.

00:48:02.694 --> 00:48:03.528
Anyway,

00:48:03.611 --> 00:48:06.531
an old heartbreak
is healed through new love.

00:48:06.614 --> 00:48:08.408
It's one of those cliché stories.

00:48:08.491 --> 00:48:11.869
But I guess she failed at healing,
seeing how things turned out for Dr. Choi.

00:48:15.748 --> 00:48:16.708
Then, by any chance,

00:48:17.625 --> 00:48:21.087
do you know anything more
about Han Seol-ah's previous boyfriend?

00:48:22.380 --> 00:48:23.297
He died.

00:48:24.215 --> 00:48:25.675
I think it was somewhere
in the Middle East.

00:48:25.758 --> 00:48:28.094
I heard he died in a terrorist attack.

00:48:30.763 --> 00:48:31.848
Are you sure he's dead?

00:48:32.765 --> 00:48:33.850
Yes.

00:48:33.933 --> 00:48:35.226
I mean, it's uncommon.

00:48:35.309 --> 00:48:37.019
A terrorist attack in the Middle East.

00:48:50.241 --> 00:48:52.577
HAN SEOL-AH MEETING WITH CHAIR KIM,
AUCTION TEAM AFTERNOON MEETING

00:48:54.245 --> 00:48:55.496
HAN SEOL-AH BUSINESS TRIP

00:49:01.878 --> 00:49:04.005
LEASE SIGNING FOR LUEN PALACE UNIT 702

00:49:06.174 --> 00:49:08.718
Did you know Kim Yun-ji went to see
Yoon Seung-jae at his restaurant?

00:49:08.801 --> 00:49:10.136
On the day before the accident, at that.

00:49:12.597 --> 00:49:13.973
Why did those two meet?

00:49:17.518 --> 00:49:19.854
LEASE SIGNING FOR LUEN PALACE UNIT 702

00:49:28.905 --> 00:49:30.072
You're still here?

00:49:32.074 --> 00:49:32.992
Yeah.

00:49:34.494 --> 00:49:35.369
What are you doing?

00:49:36.370 --> 00:49:39.165
Oh, I was just organizing some files.

00:49:40.291 --> 00:49:42.460
What brings you here at this hour?

00:49:45.922 --> 00:49:47.340
I wanted to ask you something.

00:49:50.343 --> 00:49:53.429
Seung-jae once mentioned
that he took out a life insurance policy…

00:49:55.723 --> 00:49:57.475
and named you as the beneficiary.

00:49:59.936 --> 00:50:01.062
By any chance…

00:50:04.190 --> 00:50:05.399
did you receive the payout?

00:50:08.903 --> 00:50:10.321
Why do you ask?

00:50:13.115 --> 00:50:14.492
Tell me. I need to know.

00:50:17.745 --> 00:50:19.205
Come on, not you too.

00:50:21.707 --> 00:50:22.583
Did you…

00:50:25.002 --> 00:50:25.878
really love…

00:50:27.338 --> 00:50:28.422
Seung-jae?

00:50:38.683 --> 00:50:39.517
Seol-ah.

00:50:40.059 --> 00:50:42.478
What do you want me to say?

00:50:43.062 --> 00:50:45.064
Don't you think
you're being too cruel to me?

00:50:45.690 --> 00:50:46.732
No, I didn't mean--

00:50:46.816 --> 00:50:47.692
Of all people,

00:50:49.151 --> 00:50:50.570
I thought you were on my side.

00:50:53.739 --> 00:50:55.283
This is all our friendship
amounts to, huh?

00:51:20.141 --> 00:51:22.768
NONGHYUP LIFE INSURANCE

00:51:22.852 --> 00:51:24.520
INSURANCE FOR THE ONES YOU LOVE

00:51:56.177 --> 00:51:59.805
YOON SEUNG-JAE, CHOI YOUNG-HO,
A THIRD MAN?

00:52:02.016 --> 00:52:04.060
HAN SEOL-AH

00:52:26.165 --> 00:52:28.918
"TERRORIST BOMB ATTACK IN SYRIA
KILLS KOREAN MAN"

00:52:31.337 --> 00:52:32.213
1 KOREAN AID WORKER KILLED

00:52:32.296 --> 00:52:34.173
On the 14th in Raqqa, Syria,

00:52:34.256 --> 00:52:37.218
a terrorist attack was carried out
by an armed group called IS,

00:52:37.301 --> 00:52:39.720
claiming the life of a Korean aid worker

00:52:39.804 --> 00:52:41.889
and adding to the grief of this tragedy.

00:52:41.973 --> 00:52:46.644
The attack took place in an area
controlled by IS-affiliated militants,

00:52:46.727 --> 00:52:51.232
and reports say a powerful explosion
killed dozens of people.

00:52:52.775 --> 00:52:56.237
THE DECEASED WAS A KOREAN NGO WORKER
PROVIDING HUMANITARIAN AID…

00:52:56.821 --> 00:52:58.572
They consigned it under my name?

00:52:58.656 --> 00:53:01.826
Yes, they insisted
that it be delivered to you.

00:53:11.210 --> 00:53:12.545
It's called…

00:53:13.462 --> 00:53:15.172
An Orphan from Syria.

00:54:38.172 --> 00:54:39.048
Nice painting.

00:54:42.968 --> 00:54:44.887
Unauthorized personnel
aren't allowed in here.

00:54:44.970 --> 00:54:45.971
Please leave.

00:54:49.642 --> 00:54:50.643
Seven years ago,

00:54:51.769 --> 00:54:54.063
there was a woman who had a boyfriend.

00:54:55.022 --> 00:54:57.066
The man worked
for an international relief organization

00:54:57.149 --> 00:54:59.068
that often went into
dangerous conflict zones.

00:55:00.861 --> 00:55:04.156
He took out a life insurance policy
for the woman he loved.

00:55:04.240 --> 00:55:05.324
The policy

00:55:06.117 --> 00:55:08.285
was set to pay out 200 million won
upon his death.

00:55:12.039 --> 00:55:14.250
He died in a terrorist attack in Syria.

00:55:19.004 --> 00:55:22.007
But the woman
couldn't collect the payout. Why?

00:55:23.968 --> 00:55:26.428
Because he suddenly canceled the policy.

00:55:28.472 --> 00:55:30.099
She must've been devastated.

00:55:31.225 --> 00:55:32.393
She lost her lover

00:55:33.352 --> 00:55:34.562
and the payout.

00:55:36.355 --> 00:55:39.733
Following the incident,
she became depressed and sought therapy.

00:55:41.694 --> 00:55:44.488
But who knows if she was
actually depressed or just pretending?

00:55:46.991 --> 00:55:47.867
And this is when

00:55:47.950 --> 00:55:50.035
a certain psychiatrist
makes his appearance.

00:55:50.119 --> 00:55:53.038
He fell in love with the woman
while trying to help her heal.

00:55:53.122 --> 00:55:54.456
ION MENTAL CLINIC
DIRECTOR CHOI YOUNG-HO

00:55:55.916 --> 00:55:59.003
He also took out a life insurance policy
and named her the beneficiary.

00:55:59.587 --> 00:56:00.838
But a few days before his suicide,

00:56:01.714 --> 00:56:02.923
he canceled the policy.

00:56:05.676 --> 00:56:07.803
The restaurant CEO
who got into an accident on the river

00:56:07.887 --> 00:56:09.680
also canceled his policy before he died.

00:56:14.101 --> 00:56:17.438
The woman lost three men
but gained nothing.

00:56:19.857 --> 00:56:22.568
But unlike her,
I gained something from these three cases.

00:56:24.278 --> 00:56:25.905
If you love Han Seol-ah…

00:56:28.741 --> 00:56:29.742
you die.

00:56:32.077 --> 00:56:33.078
And that's a fact.

00:56:41.921 --> 00:56:44.590
I'm sure those men wanted to save
the deeply hurt woman.

00:56:44.673 --> 00:56:47.051
You see, men tend to go blind

00:56:47.134 --> 00:56:49.053
once they fall in love.

00:56:49.136 --> 00:56:52.097
That's why they gave their all to her,
even their lives.

00:56:54.516 --> 00:56:55.601
In those men's eyes,

00:56:57.019 --> 00:56:59.104
she must've seemed like such a pitiful,

00:57:00.564 --> 00:57:02.274
helpless woman.

00:57:08.530 --> 00:57:10.032
Then, in your eyes,

00:57:10.950 --> 00:57:13.118
how does that woman appear right now?

00:57:30.344 --> 00:57:31.303
I'm not sure.

00:57:33.639 --> 00:57:34.723
I can't really see her.

00:57:47.987 --> 00:57:48.946
Can you see her now?

00:57:52.658 --> 00:57:54.201
That pitiful woman…

00:57:58.706 --> 00:58:00.958
Does she look like the kind of woman

00:58:01.917 --> 00:58:03.585
who wants to be saved by another man?

00:58:15.347 --> 00:58:17.391
You said anyone who loves me ends up dead.

00:58:18.350 --> 00:58:20.728
You talk as if
you know everything about me.

00:58:25.816 --> 00:58:27.484
Then tell me.

00:58:29.111 --> 00:58:30.612
Who's next?

00:58:32.156 --> 00:58:33.365
Next?

00:58:41.457 --> 00:58:43.500
The next man who'll fall in love…

00:58:47.546 --> 00:58:48.589
with Han Seol-ah.

00:59:07.066 --> 00:59:10.361
SPECIAL THANKS TO LEE ELIJAH
AND HA SEOKJIN FOR THEIR APPEARANCE

00:59:33.675 --> 00:59:35.594
The pain of becoming a mistress.

00:59:36.303 --> 00:59:38.972
The man who doesn't deliver
on his promise.

00:59:39.056 --> 00:59:40.849
What did you gain
from the deaths of those men?

00:59:41.308 --> 00:59:43.852
Does knowing that change anything?

00:59:45.020 --> 00:59:46.355
I think I know where it is.

00:59:48.982 --> 00:59:50.692
It felt like I was falling in love.

00:59:50.776 --> 00:59:53.821
So? Did you decide on your next man?

00:59:54.446 --> 00:59:57.324
Step aside if you don't want to cause
any misunderstandings.

00:59:58.992 --> 01:00:00.119
Who exactly are you?

01:00:01.203 --> 01:00:02.830
Why did you approach me?

01:00:05.791 --> 01:00:07.793
Subtitle: Jenny Kim